description:
With the Assembly elections getting closer, the political battleground is heating up in all five poll-bound states. On Friday, Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath filed his nomination papers from Gorakhpur Urban seat. In Punjab, the ruling Congress party is gearing up to announce its chief ministerial candidate on Sunday. Meanwhile, in Goa, the Aam Aadmi Party released an eight-point agenda for the welfare of Scheduled Tribes.
The Assembly elections in Uttar Pradesh, Punjab, Goa, Manipur and Uttarakhand will be held between February 10 and March 7. The votes will be counted on March 10. Follow IndiaToday.in for LIVE updates on the elections.
